            <section ID="ID1">
               <id root="02e463ce-fea7-4ca5-b98d-aee73d1b356b"/>
               <code code="34089-3" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DESCRIPTION SECTION"/>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph ID="ID20">Methylergonovine Maleate is a semi-synthetic ergot alkaloid used for the prevention and control of postpartum hemorrhage.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Methylergonovine Maleate Tablets, USP is available in tablets for oral ingestion containing 0.2 mg methylergonovine maleate.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="bold">Tablets</content>
                  </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="italics">Active ingredient: </content>Methylergonovine maleate, USP, 0.2 mg.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>
                     <content styleCode="italics">Inactive ingredients: </content>acacia, corn starch, gelatin, lactose monohydrate, methylparaben, microcrystalline cellulose, povidone, propylparaben, stearic acid, and tartaric acid.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Chemically, methylergonovine maleate is designated as ergoline-8-carboxamide, 9, 10-didehydro-<content styleCode="italics">N</content>-[1-(hydroxymethyl) propyl]-6-methyl-, [8β(<content styleCode="italics">S</content>)]-, (Z)-2-butenedioate (1:1) (salt). Its structural formula is:</paragraph>
                  <renderMultiMedia referencedObject="MM1"/>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20171113"/>
               <component>
                  <observationMedia ID="MM1">
                     <text>structure.png</text>
                     <value xsi:type="ED" mediaType="image/jpeg">
                        <reference value="16ee131d-1b49-4b13-9e23-e915401e7093-01.jpg"/>
